: The Role of Grammar (8–14-Year-Olds) -- t29. Online Sentence Processing in Children and Adults: General and Specifi c Constraints. A Crosslinguistic Study in Four Languages -- t30. A Personal Tribute0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume aims to provide a broad view of second language acquisition within a comparative perspective that addresses results concerning adult and child learners across a variety of source and target languages. It brings together contributions at the forefront of language acquisition research that consider a wide range of open questions: What are the precise mechanisms underlying acquisition? How can we characterize learners’ initial state and predict their degree of final achievement? What role do specific (typological) properties of source and target languages play? How does fossilization occur? How does the relative complexity of cognitive systems in adult and child learners affect acquisition? Does language learning influence cognitive organization? Can language learning shed light on our general understanding of human language and language processing?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLanguage acquisition. 0aSecond language acquisition. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aClive Perdue.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  aattainment in language learning.  acognition and language acquisition.  afossilization .  alanguage processing.  asecond language learning.  asuccessful language learning.1 aAleksandrova, Tatiana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndorno, Cecilia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBartning, Inge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBec